---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="ToolPolaris — AI Tool Rankings for Marketing Professionals"
  description="ToolPolaris cuts through 3,000+ AI tools to give marketing professionals honest, role-specific rankings. No hype. Find the stack that actually fits how you work."
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">AI Tools for Marketing Professionals</div>
      <h1>
        Stop Wasting Hours on AI Tools That Don&rsquo;t Fit
        <em>How Marketers Actually Work.</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="sub">
        ToolPolaris cuts through 3,000+ AI tools to give marketing professionals honest,
        role-specific rankings &mdash; so you can build a stack that makes you faster,
        without the trial-and-error tax.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta-group">
        <a href="/categories/" class="btn-primary">Find Your AI Stack &rarr;</a>
        <a href="/tools/"      class="btn-secondary">Browse All Tools</a>
      </div>
      <p class="hero-micro">Free to use &middot; No signup required &middot; Updated weekly</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TRUST BAR -->
  <div class="trust-bar">
    <div class="container trust-bar-inner">
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="star">✦</span> 200+ tools reviewed</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="star">✦</span> 40+ marketing use cases</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="star">✦</span> Updated weekly</div>
      <div class="trust-item"><span class="star">✦</span> Editorial-first rankings</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- BENEFITS -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Why ToolPolaris</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Recommendations that actually fit<br>how you do your job</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Generic &ldquo;best AI tools&rdquo; lists are written for everyone &mdash; which means they&rsquo;re optimised for no one.</p>
      <div class="benefits-grid">
        <div class="benefit-card">
          <div class="benefit-icon">🎯</div>
          <h3>Rankings built around your role, not everyone&rsquo;s</h3>
          <p>A content marketer, a paid media manager, and a marketing ops lead have completely different workflows. ToolPolaris gives each of them different recommendations &mdash; because the right tool depends on how you actually spend your day.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-card">
          <div class="benefit-icon">🔍</div>
          <h3>We tell you what the tool actually does &mdash; and doesn&rsquo;t</h3>
          <p>Every tool has a homepage that makes it sound transformational. We test against real marketing workflows and give you the honest read: what it&rsquo;s genuinely good at, where it falls short, and whether the price is worth it at your stage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="benefit-card">
          <div class="benefit-icon">🔄</div>
          <h3>Kept current as the landscape shifts &mdash; weekly</h3>
          <p>A tool that was best-in-class six months ago may have been leapfrogged or had its pricing restructured. We track the AI tools space continuously and update rankings when something meaningful changes. No stale advice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CATEGORIES -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Browse by Use Case</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Find tools for your specific workflow</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Pick the use case closest to what you actually need &mdash; not a broad category that covers everything.</p>
      <div class="categories-grid">
        <a href="/tools/ai-writing-tools-marketers/"    class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">✍️</span> AI Writing</a>
        <a href="/tools/ai-social-media-tools/"         class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">📱</span> Social Media</a>
        <a href="/tools/ai-seo-tools-marketers/"        class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">🔎</span> SEO &amp; Content</a>
        <a href="/tools/ai-ad-copy-tools/"              class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">📣</span> Ad Copy</a>
        <a href="/tools/ai-analytics-tools-marketers/"  class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">📊</span> Analytics</a>
        <a href="/tools/ai-email-marketing-tools/"      class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">📧</span> Email Marketing</a>
        <a href="/tools/ai-design-tools-marketers/"     class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">🎨</span> Design &amp; Creative</a>
        <a href="/tools/ai-research-tools-marketers/"   class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">🧠</span> Market Research</a>
        <a href="/tools/ai-video-tools-marketers/"      class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">🎬</span> Video &amp; Repurposing</a>
        <a href="/tools/ai-automation-tools-marketers/" class="category-pill"><span class="emoji">⚡</span> Automation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TESTIMONIALS -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">What Marketers Say</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Finally, rankings you can trust</h2>
      <div class="testimonials-grid">
        <div class="testimonial">
          <p>&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve bookmarked a lot of AI tool sites. ToolPolaris is the first one where I actually trust the rankings aren&rsquo;t just whoever paid the most.&rdquo;</p>
          <div class="testimonial-author">Rachel M. &mdash; Marketing Manager, SaaS</div>
        </div>
        <div class="testimonial">
          <p>&ldquo;Finally found a solid AI writing tool recommendation that accounted for the fact that I&rsquo;m writing B2B technical content, not generic blog posts.&rdquo;</p>
          <div class="testimonial-author">James T. &mdash; Content Strategist, B2B Tech</div>
        </div>
        <div class="testimonial">
          <p>&ldquo;Saved me at least three bad software subscriptions this quarter. The &lsquo;not worth it&rsquo; verdicts are just as valuable as the recommendations.&rdquo;</p>
          <div class="testimonial-author">Priya S. &mdash; Head of Marketing, Ecommerce</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA / NEWSLETTER -->
  <section class="cta-section" id="newsletter">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to stop guessing and build a stack that actually works?</h2>
      <p>Browse role-specific AI tool rankings. Free, no signup required.</p>
      <a href="/categories/" class="btn-primary" style="font-size:1.05rem; padding: 16px 32px;">
        Find Your AI Stack &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Good questions we get a lot</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item"><details><summary>How does ToolPolaris make money?</summary><p>We earn affiliate commissions when you sign up for a tool through one of our links. This is disclosed clearly on every page. Our rankings are editorial-first &mdash; we only recommend tools we&rsquo;d genuinely point a colleague toward, because our long-term revenue depends on reader trust, not on steering you toward the highest-paying affiliate partner.</p></details></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><details><summary>Are your rankings based on actual testing or just aggregated specs?</summary><p>Every featured tool has been evaluated against real marketing workflows &mdash; not spec sheets. We assess tools on the tasks marketers actually use them for: writing, campaign planning, performance analysis, reporting, and automation. Where we haven&rsquo;t tested something hands-on, we say so clearly and lean on verified user data instead.</p></details></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><details><summary>How often are rankings updated?</summary><p>We review rankings monthly and publish updates whenever a tool releases a meaningful change, raises or cuts pricing, or a new competitor enters a category. Every article shows the date it was last reviewed &mdash; so you always know how fresh the information is.</p></details></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><details><summary>Why trust this over G2, Capterra, or Product Hunt?</summary><p>G2 and Capterra aggregate user reviews &mdash; useful for social proof, but noisy, gameable, and not filtered by profession or use case. Product Hunt surfaces what&rsquo;s new, not what&rsquo;s proven. ToolPolaris gives you editorial rankings built specifically around marketing workflows. Different purpose, different depth.</p></details></div>
        <div class="faq-item"><details><summary>Can I request a tool review or suggest a category you&rsquo;re missing?</summary><p>Yes &mdash; use the <a href="/contact/" style="color:var(--brand-accent);">contact form</a> or reply to any of our emails. We prioritise review requests from readers, since that tells us what the market actually needs covered. If a tool you&rsquo;re evaluating isn&rsquo;t on the site yet, submit it and we&rsquo;ll aim to publish within two weeks.</p></details></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* HERO */
  .hero { background: var(--brand-dark); padding: 100px 0 80px; text-align: center; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
  .hero::before { content: '★'; position: absolute; top: -40px; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); font-size: 320px; opacity: 0.03; color: var(--brand-accent); pointer-events: none; }
  .hero-eyebrow { display: inline-block; background: rgba(245,166,35,0.15); color: var(--brand-accent); font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 1.2px; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 6px 14px; border-radius: 20px; margin-bottom: 24px; }
  .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.4rem); font-weight: 800; color: #fff; line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.5px; max-width: 780px; margin: 0 auto 20px; }
  .hero h1 em { color: var(--brand-accent); font-style: normal; }
  .hero p.sub { font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.2rem); color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72); max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto 36px; }
  .hero-cta-group { display: flex; gap: 12px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .hero-micro { font-size: 0.8rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.42); margin-top: 14px; }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .hero { padding: 72px 0 56px; } }

  /* TRUST BAR */
  .trust-bar { background: #fff; border-bottom: 1px solid #e8ecf0; padding: 20px 0; }
  .trust-bar-inner { display: flex; gap: 32px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; }
  .trust-item { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-muted); }
  .trust-item .star { color: var(--brand-accent); }

  /* BENEFITS */
  .benefits-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 28px; margin-top: 52px; }
  .benefit-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #e4e9f0; border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 32px 28px; transition: box-shadow .2s, transform .2s; }
  .benefit-card:hover { box-shadow: 0 8px 28px rgba(15,31,61,0.1); transform: translateY(-2px); }
  .benefit-icon { width: 44px; height: 44px; background: rgba(245,166,35,0.12); border-radius: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 1.3rem; margin-bottom: 18px; }
  .benefit-card h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .benefit-card p  { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.65; }

  /* CATEGORIES */
  .categories-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(180px, 1fr)); gap: 14px; margin-top: 44px; }
  .category-pill { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; background: #fff; border: 1px solid #e4e9f0; border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 14px 18px; text-decoration: none; color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 0.875rem; font-weight: 600; transition: border-color .2s, box-shadow .2s; }
  .category-pill:hover { border-color: var(--brand-accent); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(245,166,35,0.12); }
  .category-pill .emoji { font-size: 1.1rem; }

  /* TESTIMONIALS */
  .testimonials-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap: 24px; margin-top: 48px; }
  .testimonial { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #e4e9f0; border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 28px 26px; position: relative; }
  .testimonial::before { content: '\201C'; position: absolute; top: 16px; left: 22px; font-size: 3rem; line-height: 1; color: var(--brand-accent); opacity: .4; font-family: Georgia, serif; }
  .testimonial p { font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text-primary); margin-top: 12px; font-style: italic; }
  .testimonial-author { margin-top: 18px; font-size: 0.82rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-muted); }


  /* CTA */
  .cta-section { background: var(--brand-dark); text-align: center; padding: 80px 0; }
  .cta-section h2 { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.4rem); font-weight: 800; color: #fff; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto 16px; letter-spacing: -0.3px; }
  .cta-section p  { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65); font-size: 1rem; max-width: 460px; margin: 0 auto 32px; }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-list { margin-top: 44px; max-width: 740px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid #e4e9f0; padding: 22px 0; }
  .faq-item:first-child { border-top: 1px solid #e4e9f0; }
  details summary { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; gap: 12px; }
  details summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  details summary::after { content: '+'; font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 400; color: var(--brand-accent); flex-shrink: 0; transition: transform .2s; }
  details[open] summary::after { transform: rotate(45deg); }
  details p { margin-top: 14px; font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.7; }
</style>
